 very short. Let us assume that \u2206b is the width of\n\nthe energy-band whose levels En are coupled by Wn,n0 to the initial level En0.", "embedding": [0.008126925, 0.009929457, 0.041296035, 0.017845891, 0.0105269905, -0.026515402, -0.034523617, -0.022162266, -0.07158207, 0.09298096, 0.04790304, -0.015947646, 0.0084771495, -0.0436921, 0.0023758335, 0.027187252, -0.020761054, -0.018945156, -0.07135435, -0.002092963, 0.03895782, 0.007857377, -0.06731919, -0.028566798, -0.03464465, 0.038068652, 0.028868362, 0.024729034, 0.057894867, 0.07384005, 0.07093277, -0.04230245, 0.026467348, -0.028667646, -0.0006041449, 0.010071989, -0.002181559, -0.013351565, 0.027838064, -0.041767765, 0.039382324, 8.20442e-05, 0.01183937, 0.016643196, -0.04276326, -0.025076868, -0.033289965, -0.0131960865, -0.026133325, -0.08258156, -0.0033174453, -0.011824374, 0.015285454, -0.026624486, 0.015872002, -0.012474999, -0.0070062415, 0.019539589, -0.026781475, 0.020176817, 0.05617527, -0.022344606, 0.035475086, -0.026621632, 0.012994349, 0.081042856, -0.0060755587, 0.046779476, -0.029252673, -0.052510288, -0.007771649, -0.048815645, 0.007855055, 0.021103445, -0.041499395, 0.037974216, 0.014330955, -0.011132544, -0.060883377, 0.009302761, -0.006851057, -0.036549415, -0.030123645, -0.008507175, 0.0006626421, -0.015568725, 0.011726886, 0.010789392, 0.00067835936, 0.024451967, 0.021359965, 0.031943627, -0.019292021, -0.022387264, -0.009580418, 0.028661381, -0.006009836, 0.0006339041, 0.037649184, 0.02419354, -0.014104706, 0.03136199, -0.018851982, 0.04620287, -0.05434425, 0.033241652, 0.010311687, 0.01241714, -0.040225044, -0.076108344, 0.0052773138, -0.00029043702, 0.016233945, 0.01332925, 0.011404872, 0.04316812, 0.023200233, 0.014817641, 0.0021226835, 0.0031982665, 0.016796168, 0.013979325, 0.058089394, 0.040640328, 0.035020724, 0.0049035745, -0.0024003966, 0.023804214, -0.043212112, 0.0096634915, 0.0017655906, -0.009690748, -0.0032267177, 0.019301236, -0.0128294155, 0.027311996, 0.004571619, 0.00